Task 2: Detecting Data Leaks Using SQL Injection Protection 
Project Title
Cloud-Based Data Leak Prevention System Using SQL Injection Detection and Protection
1. Project Overview
SQL Injection is one of the most common cyberattacks where attackers insert malicious SQL queries into application inputs to gain unauthorized access to a database.
This project aims to:
Detect SQL Injection attempts
Prevent unauthorized database access
Protect sensitive user information
Secure cloud-hosted applications
The system uses parameterized queries and input validation to stop SQL Injection attacks.
2. Problem Statement
Many web applications directly insert user input into SQL queries.
Example:
Python
query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username='" + username + "'"
An attacker can enter:
SQL
admin' OR '1'='1
Resulting query:
SQL
SELECT * FROM users
WHERE username='admin'
OR '1'='1'
Since '1'='1' is always true, the attacker may gain unauthorized access.
